@node "History040897" "04.08.97."

  04.08.97.          -  Started coding.
@endnode

@node "History050897" "05.08.97."

  05.08.97.          -  Internal release, actually not really usable.
@endnode

@node "History070897" "v0.2 07.08.97."

  07.08.97. (v0.2)   -  Fixed some bugs, fixed time measuring, added
                        display, slider and real-time commands. Many other
                        small improvements.
@endnode

@node "History080897" "v0.4 08.08.97."

  08.08.97. (v0.4)   -  Fixed bugs in display, added 'Frequency division'
                        buttons, fixed slider moving, added 'Quality'
                        buttons, fixed time measuring (now should work
                        okay)
@endnode

@node "History090897" "v0.5 09.08.97."

  09.08.97. (v0.5)   -  Disabled slider moving by one click while playing,
                        added 'Volume' scroller, added 'Reset volume to
                        default' button, some minor improvements.
@endnode

@node "History100897" "v0.6 10.08.97."

  10.08.97. (v0.6)   -  Added 'Repeat' button, blinking playing status
@endnode

@node "History120897" "v0.7 12.08.97."

  12.08.97. (v0.7)   -  Minor changes on display, added multitrack
                        selection, 'Filter' and 'Random' buttons
@endnode

@node "History150897" "v0.8 15.08.97."

  15.08.97. (v0.8)   -  Buttons redesigned. First public release.
@endnode

@node "History230897" "v0.9 23.08.97."

  23.08.97. (v0.9)   -  Fixed to work with MPEGA v3.2 (header was changed).
                        Added preferences window and 'Save configuration
                        on exit' button.
                        Added 'Process priority' slider (don't set
                        priority too high because you won't be able to
                        stop the track, or you'll have to wait a lot.
                        Priorities -1 and 0 are the best choices if you
                        have a slower Amiga)
                        Added 'Max. decoding frequency' and 'Audio mixing
                        frequency' sliders. Added 'Default track path'
                        and 'Default MPEGA path' requesters as well.
                        Added 'Save' and 'Reset' buttons and fixed a bug
                        with saving configuration.
@endnode

@node "History180997" "v1.0 18.09.97."

  18.09.97. (v1.0)   -  Fixed to work with MPEGA v3.3. Some code
                        optimizations. Added input file buffer slider and
                        AHI support (if you don't have AHI installed,
                        option will be disabled). Added audio buffer
                        support. DOS command 'Break' is no longer needed.
@endnode

@node "History291097" "v1.1 29.10.97."

  29.10.97. (v1.1)   -  Convert window. Status command is no longer needed.
                        Removed 'Select MPEGA file' requester when
                        configuration file wasn't founded (some users had
                        trouble with this) - now GUI loads default
                        parameters, and you can change them afterwards.
                        Track slider now counts in seconds. Minor changes
                        to track and volume slider positioning (should work
                        better now).
@endnode

@node "History050498" "v1.2 05.04.98."

  05.04.98. (v1.2)   -  Added PlayList editor. Configuration changed
                        again (sorry...). First file scanning is now a
                        little bit slower due to a total time calculation,
                        but should not be the problem (you can save the
                        playlist anyway). Percentage counter now uses
                        integer arithmetic, which results in more reliable
                        timing. Some small improvements and bug fixes.
                        AmigaGuide documentation made.
@endnode

@node "History101099" "v1.3 08.12.99."

  08.12.99. (v1.3)

  -  Fixed various bugs.
  -  Added ID3 TAG editor
  -  Scaning song is now much faster
  -  Moving slider while song is playing now show seek time on main window
  -  Pause between songs is shorter
  -  Play and Next buttons are replaced
  -  After pause, song can be resumed with pause again or with play button
  -  Added fast moving song in PlayList while holding Left SHIFT
  -  Added minimized and compact mode ('F1' and 'F2')
  -  Added hotkeys 'e'-Eject, 'p'-Playlist, 'Enter'-Play, 'space'-Pause,
     'Esc'-Stop
  -  Added Startup PlayList option
  -  When add new song to PlayList, moving slider or pause will play wrong
     song. FIXED
  -  Click inside slider now move song to that position immediately
  -  File selector now has picture
  -  Preferences window has changed. Now has enough place for many options.
  -  Added background picture (at this moment it is file dgui.bsh located
     in PROGDIR:, but later you can choose any file). Picture is loading
     via datatypes, so it can be any format (ILBM, JPG, BMP.. etc.)
  -  Added choosing remap colors and precision for background picture, if you
     don't have true color graphics
  -  GUI now take care of title font height
  -  Configuration is now saved in ENVARC:DiamondGUI.cfg, so you can delete
     old configuration in s: . Config is changed for last time, I hope.
     In future versions new config should recognize old one.



@endnode

